&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 300; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Samsara (NYSE: IOT) is the pioneer of the Connected Operations™ Cloud, which is a platform that enables organizations that depend on physical operations to harness Internet of Things (IoT) data to develop actionable insights and improve their operations. At Samsara, we are helping improve the safety, efficiency and sustainability of the physical operations that power our global economy. Representing more than 40% of global GDP, these industries are the infrastructure of our planet, including agriculture, construction, field services, transportation, and manufacturing — and we are excited to help digitally transform their operations at scale.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 300; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Working at Samsara means you’ll help define the future of physical operations and be on a team that’s shaping an exciting array of product solutions, including Video-Based Safety, Vehicle Telematics, Apps and Driver Workflows, and Equipment Monitoring. As part of a recently public company, you’ll have the autonomy and support to make an impact as we build for the long term.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Shipping and Receiving Logistics Manager is responsible for overseeing, directing, and managing all aspects of the operations for the Headquarters mailroom. This includes handling key parcel carrier accounts, developing and implementing programs to optimize logistics workflows, and ensuring seamless coordination between physical and digital mail processes. This role also ensures efficient processing, tracking, and delivery of all inbound and outbound shipments, while maintaining meticulous records and inventory control. A key function of this role is the accurate allocation, tracking, and reconciliation of parcel billing, ensuring shipping costs are properly assigned to the correct cost centers or departments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a hybrid position requiring 5 days per week in our San Francisco Office. Relocation assistance will not be provided for this role.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You should apply if:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You want to impact the industries that run our world:&lt;/strong&gt; Your efforts will result in real-world impact—helping to keep the lights on, get food into grocery stores, reduce emissions, and most importantly, ensure workers return home safely.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You are the architect of your own career:&lt;/strong&gt; If you put in the work, this role won’t be your last at Samsara. We set up our employees for success and have built a culture that encourages rapid career development, countless opportunities to experiment and master your craft in a hyper growth environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re energized by our opportunity:&lt;/strong&gt; The vision we have to digitize large sectors of the global economy requires your full focus and best efforts to bring forth creative, ambitious ideas for our customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You want to be with the best: &lt;/strong&gt;At Samsara, we win together, celebrate together and support each other. You will be surrounded by a high-calibre team that will encourage you to do your best.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and implement efficient shipping and receiving procedures and protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the daily operations of the Headquarters shipping and receiving mailroom,&amp;nbsp; processing&amp;nbsp; all incoming and outgoing mail, packages, and freight.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer and oversee all corporate shipping accounts, ensuring cost-effectiveness and adherence to company policies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with various departments to facilitate the timely and accurate delivery of materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track shipments and maintain accurate records of all transactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and audit onsite inventory, supplies and equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Resolve shipping and receiving discrepancies or issues promptly and effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with all applicable safety regulations and standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and supervise, train, and mentor mailroom staff, providing guidance and support as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare comprehensive reports on shipping and receiving activities as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and allocate monthly UPS billings according to reference numbers, and provide detailed cost breakdowns to accounting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage corporate UPS account users, including adding and removing profiles as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and launch global shipping programs and solutions.Creating and implementing standard operating procedures (SOPs) for shipping, receiving and storage services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Print incoming documents, pack shipments, and create shipping labels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion, role model, and embed Samsara’s cultural principles (Focus on Customer Success, Build for the Long Term, Adopt a Growth Mindset, Be Inclusive, Win as a Team) as we scale globally and across new offices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hire, develop and lead an inclusive, engaged, and high performing team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum requirements for the role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5+ years of experience in shipping/receiving logistics or related fields.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity and training in the shipping of dangerous goods and hazardous materials (HAZMAT).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive knowledge of shipping and logistics processes and regulations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational, project management, and time-management abilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to lift and move heavy packages and materials.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with shipping software (UPS CampusShip, FedEx Ship Manager), envoy, financial tools, and ERP systems and SOX compliances&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Can be onsite Monday-Friday in our San Francisco Office.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;An ideal candidate also has:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to manage and supervise a team effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of air parcel shipment networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thorough knowledge of correctly preparing commercial invoices across all major parcel systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing/developing a shipping and receiving operations program from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
